100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 15, 1926, British Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin announced a new government initiative aimed at addressing unemployment, a pressing issue in post-war Britain. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition intensified as various cities reported rising crime rates linked to illegal speakeasies. Meanwhile, tensions in the Middle East escalated as reports emerged of violent clashes in Palestine, highlighting the region's growing instability.
